--------------------------------------------------
GENERAL PRINCIPLES
--------------------------------------------------

Always prefer composition over inheritance.

Keep code modular.

Avoid duplication.

Follow SOLID.

Follow DRY.

Follow KISS.

Think about long-term maintenance.

Whenever there are multiple implementation possibilities, explain the trade-offs before suggesting one.

If any requirement is ambiguous, ask clarifying questions before writing code.

Always consider future scalability without prematurely optimizing.

Every solution should be production-ready.
